<paragraph blockId="54.[151,1437,150,717]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,294,320]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species was previously recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[850,996,295,321]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Abu-Zoherah, R. &amp; Al-Taher, K. &amp; Tilkian, S." box="[1038,1335,295,321]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" refId="ref33021" refString="Abu-Zoherah, R., Al-Taher, K. &amp; Tilkian, S. (1993) List of Insects Recorded from Saudi Arabia. Ministry of Agriculture and Water, National Agriculture and Water Research Center, Kingdom of Saudi Arabia, Riyadh, Academic Publishing &amp; Press, Ministry of Agriculture and Water, Riyadh, 394 pp." type="book" year="1993">
Abu-Zoherah 
<emphasis box="[1197,1246,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">et al</emphasis>
. (1993)
</bibRefCitation>
and also recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[318,396,331,357]" name="Yemen" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Yemen</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Smit, J. T. &amp; van Harten, A. &amp; Ketelaar, R." box="[411,598,331,357]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" refId="ref40237" refString="Smit, J. T., van Harten, A. &amp; Ketelaar, R. (2017) Order Diptera, family Syrphidae the hoverflies of the Arabian Peninsula. In: van Harten, A. (Eds.), Arthropod fauna of the UAE. Vol. 6. Department of the President's Affairs, Abu Dhabi, pp. 572 - 612." type="book" year="2017">
Smit 
<emphasis box="[473,523,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
). It was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[870,959,331,357]" name="Senegal" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Senegal</collectingCountry>
and also known from the following areas; Palaearctic Region: (it is restricted to the Mediterranean subregion and Middle East, eastwards to Ahvaz in the south-western 
<collectingCountry box="[315,360,403,429]" name="Iran" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lyneborg, L. &amp; Barkemeyer, W." box="[374,721,402,429]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" pagination="1 - 224" refId="ref37423" refString="Lyneborg, L. &amp; Barkemeyer, W. (2005) A world revision of the genus Syritta Le Peletier &amp; Serville, 1828 (Diptera: Syrphidae). Entomonograph, 15, 1 - 224." type="journal article" year="2005">Lyneborg &amp; Barkemeyer 2005</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[739,826,403,429]" name="Algeria" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Algeria</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[836,924,403,429]" name="France" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Corsica</collectingCountry>
, Crete, 
<collectingCountry box="[1010,1094,403,429]" name="Cyprus" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Cyprus</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1104,1174,403,429]" name="Egypt" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Egypt</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1185,1264,403,429]" name="France" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">France</collectingCountry>
, Greek Islands, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,289,439,465]" name="Italy Jordan" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Italy Jordan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[302,403,439,465]" name="Lebanon" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Lebanon</collectingCountry>
, (Sicily), 
<collectingCountry box="[516,620,439,465]" name="Morocco" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Morocco</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[633,731,439,465]" name="Portugal" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Portugal</collectingCountry>
, Sardinia, 
<collectingCountry box="[853,920,439,465]" name="Spain" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Spain</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[932,994,439,465]" name="Syria" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Syria</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1007,1093,439,465]" name="Tunisia" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1105,1189,439,465]" name="Turkey" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Turkey</collectingCountry>
; Afrotropical Region: (
<collectingCountry box="[159,290,475,501]" name="Cape Verde" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Cape Verde</collectingCountry>
Islands, 
<collectingCountry box="[390,527,475,501]" name="Madagascar" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[538,650,475,501]" name="Mauritius" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Mauritius</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[661,806,475,501]" name="South Africa" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">South Africa</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[818,937,475,501]" name="Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">St. Helena</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[947,1025,475,501]" name="Yemen" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Yemen</collectingCountry>
); it has supposedly been introduced to Pacific Ocean (Easter Island); Nearctic Region: 
<collectingCountry box="[726,840,511,537]" name="Argentina" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Argentina</collectingCountry>
